00:29:46.760 --> 00:29:50.300 align:middle line:84%
we wiped up the planet,
for good or bad.

00:29:50.300 --> 00:29:52.050 align:middle line:90%
And that now is our problem.

00:29:52.050 --> 00:29:55.880 align:middle line:84%
We've got this egoic structure,
and you can see it everywhere

00:29:55.880 --> 00:29:58.310 align:middle line:90%
you look.

00:29:58.310 --> 00:30:00.990 align:middle line:90%
There's a big ego sitting there.

00:30:00.990 --> 00:30:03.320 align:middle line:84%
And this ego is what's
running the process

00:30:03.320 --> 00:30:04.550 align:middle line:90%
and screwing everything up.

00:30:04.550 --> 00:30:12.590 align:middle line:90%


00:30:12.590 --> 00:30:15.800 align:middle line:84%
>> We've lost ourselves
in objective experience.

00:30:15.800 --> 00:30:19.490 align:middle line:84%
We have allowed ourselves
to become immersed

00:30:19.490 --> 00:30:22.340 align:middle line:84%
in and therefore,
apparently limited

00:30:22.340 --> 00:30:25.070 align:middle line:84%
by our objective
experience to the extent

00:30:25.070 --> 00:30:26.660 align:middle line:84%
that that's what
we think we are.

00:30:26.660 --> 00:30:30.090 align:middle line:84%
We think I am this bundle of
thoughts, images, feelings,

00:30:30.090 --> 00:30:33.240 align:middle line:84%
memories, activities,
relationships.

00:30:33.240 --> 00:30:39.240 align:middle line:84%
Now, most people are so
involved in their experience

00:30:39.240 --> 00:30:41.370 align:middle line:90%
that they don't notice.

00:30:41.370 --> 00:30:44.910 align:middle line:84%
They overlook or forget
their essential self,

00:30:44.910 --> 00:30:47.350 align:middle line:84%
and this overlooking
of ourselves,

00:30:47.350 --> 00:30:51.720 align:middle line:84%
this is the ignoring of
the essential element

00:30:51.720 --> 00:30:53.447 align:middle line:90%
of our experience.

00:30:53.447 --> 00:31:11.870 align:middle line:90%


00:31:11.870 --> 00:31:14.600 align:middle line:84%
What is there for
him to do to stop

00:31:14.600 --> 00:31:16.520 align:middle line:84%
trying to put an
end to his suffering

00:31:16.520 --> 00:31:20.150 align:middle line:84%
by seeking to change his
activities, relationships,

00:31:20.150 --> 00:31:22.880 align:middle line:84%
et cetera, but to
investigate who he truly is.

00:31:22.880 --> 00:31:26.289 align:middle line:84%
And to begin with, that will
require some exploration.

00:31:26.289 --> 00:31:28.285 align:middle line:90%


00:31:28.285 --> 00:31:32.277 align:middle line:90%
[CHANTING]

00:31:32.277 --> 00:32:14.700 align:middle line:90%


00:32:14.700 --> 00:32:18.670 align:middle line:84%
>> The root causes of suffering
can be described in many ways.

00:32:18.670 --> 00:32:21.200 align:middle line:84%
And different
spiritual traditions

00:32:21.200 --> 00:32:27.410 align:middle line:84%
may describe it differently, but
certainly, the sense of the ego

00:32:27.410 --> 00:32:31.870 align:middle line:90%
self is definitely--

00:32:31.870 --> 00:32:34.750 align:middle line:84%
you could call that
basic ignorance

00:32:34.750 --> 00:32:39.610 align:middle line:84%
where we've created this
notion, this sense of self,

00:32:39.610 --> 00:32:43.750 align:middle line:84%
this sense of I, very deeply
conditioned, really deeply

00:32:43.750 --> 00:32:47.050 align:middle line:90%
habituated.

00:32:47.050 --> 00:32:48.340 align:middle line:90%
But it's really a construct.

00:32:48.340 --> 00:32:51.256 align:middle line:90%
[CHANTING]

00:32:51.256 --> 00:32:54.660 align:middle line:90%


00:32:54.660 --> 00:32:56.375 align:middle line:84%
And of course, the
meditative process

00:32:56.375 --> 00:33:00.830 align:middle line:84%
is to see that this
very notion is illusory,

00:33:00.830 --> 00:33:05.880 align:middle line:84%
that there's a conventional
meaning to the sense of self

00:33:05.880 --> 00:33:08.840 align:middle line:84%
and I, and it has
a use, but it also

00:33:08.840 --> 00:33:11.840 align:middle line:84%
has a danger because
as long as there's

00:33:11.840 --> 00:33:16.430 align:middle line:84%
that view, then
what is it that we

00:33:16.430 --> 00:33:18.230 align:middle line:90%
do around this sense of self?

00:33:18.230 --> 00:33:19.370 align:middle line:90%
We try to gratify it.

00:33:19.370 --> 00:33:20.240 align:middle line:90%
We defend it.

00:33:20.240 --> 00:33:21.740 align:middle line:90%
We aggrandize it.

00:33:21.740 --> 00:33:23.280 align:middle line:90%
We judge it.

00:33:23.280 --> 00:33:25.260 align:middle line:90%
We do all kinds of things.

00:33:25.260 --> 00:33:27.900 align:middle line:84%
But meditation takes
us to a deeper level

00:33:27.900 --> 00:33:29.900 align:middle line:84%
where we say, OK, what
is it that we're actually

00:33:29.900 --> 00:33:32.220 align:middle line:90%
calling self?

00:33:32.220 --> 00:33:36.470 align:middle line:84%
And when we look deeper, we
see the constituent elements

00:33:36.470 --> 00:33:37.430 align:middle line:90%
that go in.

00:33:37.430 --> 00:33:39.650 align:middle line:84%
And this is just helpful
because then we're

00:33:39.650 --> 00:33:43.790 align:middle line:84%
not so attached to this idea,
to this concept, of self.

00:33:43.790 --> 00:33:48.320 align:middle line:90%


00:33:48.320 --> 00:33:52.700 align:middle line:84%
The more we can let go of the
self-centeredness which is just

00:33:52.700 --> 00:33:54.290 align:middle line:90%
what ego means--

00:33:54.290 --> 00:34:01.130 align:middle line:84%
there is a self-center
that we gravitate around--

00:34:01.130 --> 00:34:06.710 align:middle line:84%
when we see through that,
then the natural expression

00:34:06.710 --> 00:34:09.980 align:middle line:84%
of that insight is compassion,
is connection, is love.

00:34:09.980 --> 00:34:17.830 align:middle line:90%


00:34:17.830 --> 00:34:20.889 align:middle line:84%
>> I had a dad who
is very strong.

00:34:20.889 --> 00:34:22.241 align:middle line:90%
Nothing's good enough.

00:34:22.241 --> 00:34:23.199 align:middle line:90%
You have to keep going.

00:34:23.199 --> 00:34:25.570 align:middle line:84%
You have to score more
goals, hit more home

00:34:25.570 --> 00:34:27.909 align:middle line:90%
runs, better, better, better.

00:34:27.909 --> 00:34:29.650 align:middle line:84%
Somehow, it was
a beautiful thing

00:34:29.650 --> 00:34:33.400 align:middle line:84%
because I became successful
financially and materially

00:34:33.400 --> 00:34:38.139 align:middle line:84%
and accomplished these things,
but I feel like somehow,

00:34:38.139 --> 00:34:41.580 align:middle line:84%
where I'm being drawn to
is the complete opposite.

00:34:41.580 --> 00:34:43.669 align:middle line:90%
>> [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH].

00:34:43.669 --> 00:36:27.170 align:middle line:90%


00:36:27.170 --> 00:36:30.350 align:middle line:84%
>> This ego part of myself
is so strong and so powerful.

00:36:30.350 --> 00:36:34.220 align:middle line:84%
It's been just fed for the
last 34 years of my life.

00:36:34.220 --> 00:36:36.252 align:middle line:84%
It's being fed and
fed and fed and fed,

00:36:36.252 --> 00:36:38.210 align:middle line:84%
just getting stronger
and stronger and stronger

00:36:38.210 --> 00:36:41.070 align:middle line:84%
and stronger, telling
me that I need this.

00:36:41.070 --> 00:36:41.870 align:middle line:90%
I need that.

00:36:41.870 --> 00:36:42.670 align:middle line:90%
I need this.

00:36:42.670 --> 00:36:43.520 align:middle line:90%
I need that.

00:36:43.520 --> 00:36:46.860 align:middle line:84%
And it was really overwhelming
to see like, shit,

00:36:46.860 --> 00:36:49.280 align:middle line:84%
this is causing so
much stress in my life

00:36:49.280 --> 00:36:53.450 align:middle line:84%
because I'm allowing myself
to get caught up in this race

00:36:53.450 --> 00:36:55.280 align:middle line:90%
of how can I get more stuff.

00:36:55.280 --> 00:36:59.090 align:middle line:90%


00:36:59.090 --> 00:37:03.350 align:middle line:84%
What I would really like to
hear for myself and understand

00:37:03.350 --> 00:37:05.670 align:middle line:90%
is like the suffering part.

00:37:05.670 --> 00:37:08.330 align:middle line:90%
I suffer, to be honest.

00:37:08.330 --> 00:37:11.030 align:middle line:84%
I do-- I don't know if
it's daily or weekly.

00:37:11.030 --> 00:37:12.140 align:middle line:90%
It just varies.

00:37:12.140 --> 00:37:14.370 align:middle line:84%
It's not on a
schedule or something,

00:37:14.370 --> 00:37:15.540 align:middle line:90%
but I do have anxiety.

00:37:15.540 --> 00:37:16.850 align:middle line:90%
I do feel fear.

00:37:16.850 --> 00:37:18.743 align:middle line:84%
I do feel like
sometimes, my mind

00:37:18.743 --> 00:37:19.910 align:middle line:90%
is just controlling my life.

00:37:19.910 --> 00:37:21.470 align:middle line:90%
>> Out of control, totally.

00:37:21.470 --> 00:37:23.720 align:middle line:84%
>> What can I do really
to be free from that?

00:37:23.720 --> 00:37:26.000 align:middle line:84%
>> We say we can
look at self-inquiry.

00:37:26.000 --> 00:37:30.380 align:middle line:84%
Mata Maharshi, probably the
sage of the 20th century,

00:37:30.380 --> 00:37:34.810 align:middle line:84%
said, just look for the
I just to ask, who am I,

00:37:34.810 --> 00:37:37.930 align:middle line:84%
over and over and
over and over again.

00:37:37.930 --> 00:37:40.780 align:middle line:84%
Western philosophy,
only one or two people

00:37:40.780 --> 00:37:43.180 align:middle line:84%
ever even looked at the
possibility of questioning

00:37:43.180 --> 00:37:47.020 align:middle line:90%
the I. Eastern folks did it.

00:37:47.020 --> 00:37:47.820 align:middle line:90%
Where am I?

00:37:47.820 --> 00:37:51.360 align:middle line:84%
>> During like-- meditate
and just on that "make that

00:37:51.360 --> 00:37:52.480 align:middle line:90%
my mantra" kind of thing?

00:37:52.480 --> 00:37:53.280 align:middle line:90%
Who am I?

00:37:53.280 --> 00:37:54.988 align:middle line:84%
>> No, not a mantra
though, not a mantra.

00:37:54.988 --> 00:37:57.310 align:middle line:84%
What we're trying to do
is get really curious.

00:37:57.310 --> 00:38:00.060 align:middle line:84%
>> Is it simple
enough to say like,

00:38:00.060 --> 00:38:02.640 align:middle line:84%
if we don't want
to feel suffering,

00:38:02.640 --> 00:38:05.580 align:middle line:84%
to just don't do things
that make us suffer.

00:38:05.580 --> 00:38:08.380 align:middle line:84%
>> But even more fundamental
than that is saying, OK,

00:38:08.380 --> 00:38:11.580 align:middle line:84%
let's just deconstruct
the sufferer.

00:38:11.580 --> 00:38:16.070 align:middle line:84%
If we don't have the sufferer,
there is no suffering.

00:38:16.070 --> 00:38:18.670 align:middle line:84%
There are an infinite number
of pleasures and possibilities

00:38:18.670 --> 00:38:23.530 align:middle line:84%
and desires and thoughts,
but there's only one I,

00:38:23.530 --> 00:38:27.230 align:middle line:84%
because it's there in every
thought, every desire.

00:38:27.230 --> 00:38:30.380 align:middle line:90%
Every lack, there's an I there.

00:38:30.380 --> 00:38:32.810 align:middle line:84%
And if you just keep
going after that I,

00:38:32.810 --> 00:38:34.970 align:middle line:90%
don't get sucked into stories.

00:38:34.970 --> 00:38:37.550 align:middle line:84%
Just keep coming back
into, what is this I?

00:38:37.550 --> 00:38:38.470 align:middle line:90%
Where is this I?

00:38:38.470 --> 00:38:40.610 align:middle line:90%
When I ask, where is James?

00:38:40.610 --> 00:38:41.810 align:middle line:90%
Oh, James is sitting here.

00:38:41.810 --> 00:38:43.850 align:middle line:84%
No, well, really
where is James though?

00:38:43.850 --> 00:38:46.830 align:middle line:84%
Well, James is
someplace in here.

00:38:46.830 --> 00:38:48.540 align:middle line:90%
No, he's not though.

00:38:48.540 --> 00:38:53.320 align:middle line:84%
And you keep watching, keep
asking, now, where is James?

00:38:53.320 --> 00:38:58.470 align:middle line:84%
And you find out that in fact,
James isn't a real thing.

00:38:58.470 --> 00:39:01.830 align:middle line:84%
Every time, James will meet
somebody, a different person--

00:39:01.830 --> 00:39:06.880 align:middle line:84%
you talk to Mark, or
if you talk to Anna,

00:39:06.880 --> 00:39:08.560 align:middle line:84%
there's a different
James who shows up

00:39:08.560 --> 00:39:10.243 align:middle line:90%
for those two situations.

00:39:10.243 --> 00:39:12.910 align:middle line:84%
You watch carefully, you can see
there are two different Jameses

00:39:12.910 --> 00:39:13.710 align:middle line:90%
there.

00:39:13.710 --> 00:39:15.700 align:middle line:84%
And if you watch yourself
in the course of day,

00:39:15.700 --> 00:39:17.155 align:middle line:90%
you can see lots of Jameses.

00:39:17.155 --> 00:39:20.100 align:middle line:90%


00:39:20.100 --> 00:39:21.310 align:middle line:90%
What's the deal here?

00:39:21.310 --> 00:39:28.710 align:middle line:84%
How important can James be if
he's got whole pack of them?

00:39:28.710 --> 00:39:30.170 align:middle line:90%
Which one do we believe is real?

00:39:30.170 --> 00:39:33.100 align:middle line:90%


00:39:33.100 --> 00:39:35.835 align:middle line:84%
If you put yourself
in the scanner,

00:39:35.835 --> 00:39:36.960 align:middle line:90%
you can look at your brain.

00:39:36.960 --> 00:39:42.450 align:middle line:84%
You can say, hold it, we
can't find James anyplace.

00:39:42.450 --> 00:39:45.240 align:middle line:84%
We can find lots of
Jameses, but James

00:39:45.240 --> 00:39:49.555 align:middle line:84%
is just an ad hoc entity
created as waves of energy sweep

00:39:49.555 --> 00:39:50.355 align:middle line:90%
across the cortex.

00:39:50.355 --> 00:39:54.850 align:middle line:90%


00:39:54.850 --> 00:39:57.880 align:middle line:84%
Scientifically, we can show
you there is no James there.

00:39:57.880 --> 00:40:01.610 align:middle line:90%


00:40:01.610 --> 00:40:04.550 align:middle line:84%
>> So according to all
that stuff, who is James?

00:40:04.550 --> 00:40:05.420 align:middle line:90%
Who am I?

00:40:05.420 --> 00:40:07.670 align:middle line:90%
>> Well, that's the question.

00:40:07.670 --> 00:40:11.490 align:middle line:90%
You're only now, now, now.

00:40:11.490 --> 00:40:14.040 align:middle line:90%
You aren't becoming now.

00:40:14.040 --> 00:40:15.330 align:middle line:90%
You're only now.

00:40:15.330 --> 00:40:17.220 align:middle line:90%
There is no past.

00:40:17.220 --> 00:40:19.635 align:middle line:90%
There's only this very moment.

00:40:19.635 --> 00:40:22.190 align:middle line:90%


00:40:22.190 --> 00:40:24.470 align:middle line:90%
Not I will be present now.

00:40:24.470 --> 00:40:26.670 align:middle line:90%
No, you are only there.

00:40:26.670 --> 00:40:27.470 align:middle line:90%
Only beingness.

00:40:27.470 --> 00:40:30.440 align:middle line:90%
There's no one being.

00:40:30.440 --> 00:40:31.880 align:middle line:90%
There's just beingness.

00:40:31.880 --> 00:40:39.374 align:middle line:90%


00:40:39.374 --> 00:40:42.867 align:middle line:90%
[TRANQUIL MUSIC]

00:40:42.867 --> 00:40:56.288 align:middle line:90%


00:40:56.288 --> 00:40:58.580 align:middle line:84%
>> It's difficult not to
evaluate the experience almost

00:40:58.580 --> 00:41:00.620 align:middle line:84%
aesthetically, if
you know what I mean.

00:41:00.620 --> 00:41:03.320 align:middle line:84%
Not to think of-- even having
the idea of a good meditation

00:41:03.320 --> 00:41:03.500 align:middle line:90%
here.

00:41:03.500 --> 00:41:04.400 align:middle line:84%
They're always telling
you, oh, there's

00:41:04.400 --> 00:41:05.510 align:middle line:84%
no such thing as
good meditation.

00:41:05.510 --> 00:41:06.310 align:middle line:90%
Ah, maybe.

00:41:06.310 --> 00:41:07.340 align:middle line:90%
So I know what I want.

00:41:07.340 --> 00:41:09.890 align:middle line:90%
I want cessation of self.

00:41:09.890 --> 00:41:12.170 align:middle line:90%
I want, ah, bliss.

00:41:12.170 --> 00:41:16.170 align:middle line:84%
There was nothingness for a
while because on some level,

00:41:16.170 --> 00:41:18.770 align:middle line:84%
we know I've put
this thing together.

00:41:18.770 --> 00:41:20.400 align:middle line:90%
It's not really who I am.

00:41:20.400 --> 00:41:22.650 align:middle line:84%
You stare too long in a
mirror, you freak yourself out

00:41:22.650 --> 00:41:24.002 align:middle line:90%
whether you're on acid or not.

00:41:24.002 --> 00:41:25.460 align:middle line:84%
It gets to a point
where you think,

00:41:25.460 --> 00:41:27.420 align:middle line:90%
who's looking back at me now?

00:41:27.420 --> 00:41:28.220 align:middle line:90%
Who is that?

00:41:28.220 --> 00:41:29.420 align:middle line:90%
Where is the distinction?

00:41:29.420 --> 00:41:34.840 align:middle line:90%


00:41:34.840 --> 00:41:37.500 align:middle line:84%
>> This is the process
of self-inquiry.

00:41:37.500 --> 00:41:41.190 align:middle line:84%
I would start by asking,
tell me about yourself

00:41:41.190 --> 00:41:47.020 align:middle line:84%
and chances are the person would
start with something like, I'm

00:41:47.020 --> 00:41:49.150 align:middle line:84%
a schoolteacher, and
straightaway, I would say,

00:41:49.150 --> 00:41:52.090 align:middle line:84%
no, you haven't always
been a school teacher,

00:41:52.090 --> 00:41:54.670 align:middle line:84%
and you probably won't
always be a school teacher.

00:41:54.670 --> 00:41:56.530 align:middle line:84%
So I want to know
about yourself.

00:41:56.530 --> 00:42:00.360 align:middle line:90%
Can you tell me about yourself?

00:42:00.360 --> 00:42:06.480 align:middle line:84%
So then the person might
say, well, I'm 34 years old.

00:42:06.480 --> 00:42:11.690 align:middle line:84%
Again, I would comment, but you
haven't always been 34 years.

00:42:11.690 --> 00:42:14.220 align:middle line:84%
You were still yourself
when you were 13 years old.

00:42:14.220 --> 00:42:17.960 align:middle line:84%
So yourself cannot have
any particular age.

00:42:17.960 --> 00:42:21.720 align:middle line:84%
So I'm presuming, of course,
that, that person understands.

00:42:21.720 --> 00:42:23.300 align:middle line:90%
It's very easy to understand.

00:42:23.300 --> 00:42:26.510 align:middle line:84%
Nothing extraordinary, nothing
mystical, nothing spiritual.

00:42:26.510 --> 00:42:30.740 align:middle line:84%
Just inviting the person
to go deeper and deeper

00:42:30.740 --> 00:42:35.600 align:middle line:84%
into their sense of themselves,
a sense of their being

00:42:35.600 --> 00:42:39.260 align:middle line:84%
what they've called,
I, all their life.

00:42:39.260 --> 00:42:43.380 align:middle line:84%
The person may then refer
to some bodily sensation.

00:42:43.380 --> 00:42:47.190 align:middle line:84%
Again, I would point out that
our bodily sensations change

00:42:47.190 --> 00:42:49.470 align:middle line:84%
innumerable times
throughout the day,

00:42:49.470 --> 00:42:51.210 align:middle line:90%
let alone throughout our lives.

00:42:51.210 --> 00:42:56.550 align:middle line:84%
So no actual experience of the
body is inherent to begin with.

00:42:56.550 --> 00:42:59.360 align:middle line:84%
They would describe thoughts,
feelings, and activities,

00:42:59.360 --> 00:43:02.310 align:middle line:84%
but as the conversation
went on, there

00:43:02.310 --> 00:43:06.180 align:middle line:84%
would be longer and
longer periods of silence

00:43:06.180 --> 00:43:10.680 align:middle line:84%
as they tried to find something
in their own experience which

00:43:10.680 --> 00:43:13.560 align:middle line:84%
they could say, this is
with me when I'm dreaming.

00:43:13.560 --> 00:43:15.780 align:middle line:84%
It's with me when
I'm deeply asleep.

00:43:15.780 --> 00:43:17.550 align:middle line:84%
It's with me
whatever I'm feeling.

00:43:17.550 --> 00:43:19.920 align:middle line:84%
It's with me at
whatever age I've been,

00:43:19.920 --> 00:43:22.200 align:middle line:84%
in whatever circumstance
I find myself.

00:43:22.200 --> 00:43:29.360 align:middle line:84%
So they would begin to
struggle to put a name to that.

00:43:29.360 --> 00:43:33.800 align:middle line:84%
What is it in our experience
that qualifies as I?

00:43:33.800 --> 00:43:37.850 align:middle line:84%
Obviously, no thought, no
feeling, no bodily sensation,

00:43:37.850 --> 00:43:40.640 align:middle line:84%
no activity, no
relationship, qualifies as I

00:43:40.640 --> 00:43:45.200 align:middle line:84%
because these are continually
leaving us and reappearing

00:43:45.200 --> 00:43:46.610 align:middle line:90%
and leaving us.

00:43:46.610 --> 00:43:51.860 align:middle line:84%
So the self-inquiry begins
with this tracing back

00:43:51.860 --> 00:43:53.990 align:middle line:90%
of the attention.

00:43:53.990 --> 00:43:56.210 align:middle line:90%
I'm not my thoughts.

00:43:56.210 --> 00:43:58.640 align:middle line:84%
I am that which is
aware of my thoughts.

00:43:58.640 --> 00:43:59.913 align:middle line:90%
I'm not my feelings.

00:43:59.913 --> 00:44:01.580 align:middle line:84%
I am that which is
aware of my feelings.

00:44:01.580 --> 00:44:07.910 align:middle line:84%
We trace our way back until we
get simply to that which I am.

00:44:07.910 --> 00:44:12.050 align:middle line:84%
The only element that
remains with us all the time

00:44:12.050 --> 00:44:16.850 align:middle line:84%
is our essential being or our
essential self-aware being,

00:44:16.850 --> 00:44:18.860 align:middle line:84%
and at some point, there
is this recognition,

00:44:18.860 --> 00:44:20.570 align:middle line:90%
I am pure awareness.

00:44:20.570 --> 00:44:23.030 align:middle line:84%
That's just the recognition
of our true nature.

00:44:23.030 --> 00:44:28.360 align:middle line:90%


00:44:28.360 --> 00:44:30.530 align:middle line:84%
And we've lost
touch in most cases

00:44:30.530 --> 00:44:34.190 align:middle line:84%
with our essential self which
is not a thought or a feeling,

00:44:34.190 --> 00:44:35.690 align:middle line:84%
an activity, or
relationship, and is

00:44:35.690 --> 00:44:41.000 align:middle line:84%
above all, inherently peaceful
and unconditionally fulfilled.

00:44:41.000 --> 00:44:44.910 align:middle line:84%
In other words, it is the place
in us of peace and happiness.

00:44:44.910 --> 00:44:49.490 align:middle line:84%
But most of us have overlooked
that or forgotten it

00:44:49.490 --> 00:44:55.530 align:middle line:84%
in favor of the objective
content of our experience.

00:44:55.530 --> 00:44:57.330 align:middle line:90%
>> [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH].

00:44:57.330 --> 00:46:21.000 align:middle line:90%


00:46:21.000 --> 00:46:25.245 align:middle line:84%
>> So is suffering
kind of an illusion?

00:46:25.245 --> 00:46:28.140 align:middle line:90%


00:46:28.140 --> 00:46:29.760 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:46:29.760 --> 00:46:34.170 align:middle line:90%
Very good, very good, very good.

00:46:34.170 --> 00:46:35.730 align:middle line:90%
[NON-ENGLISH SPEECH].

00:46:35.730 --> 00:46:51.510 align:middle line:90%


00:46:51.510 --> 00:46:54.410 align:middle line:90%
It's not real.

